 The police are searching for a man accused of menacing a Brooklyn subway rider with a knife on Sunday. According to the NYPD, on Sunday, November 1st, at about 5 a.m., a 19-year-old woman was on the northbound platform of the Smith-9th Street F train subway station when the suspect "displayed a knife to her."
The suspect then fled, but police released surveillance images of him and described him as about 25 to 30 years old, 5'4" and 180 pounds, with braids and was last seen wearing a black vest, gray sweater with white stripes, black jeans, and red sneakers.
